{"type":"message","id":"6600f5da","parentId":"fe2d45c7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:52:02.970Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bcnyzl2br5jk_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 153842\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: src/tic_classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to identify the most impactful single action to advance the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The key insight from the session is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem.\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC experiment requires:\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to create a script that can analyze the pulse logs and start implementing the TIC classifier. This is a file creation action that sets up the experiment framework.\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant patterns (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Identifies variant patterns (things that change)\r\n4. Measures classification accuracy\r\n\r\nThis would be a new PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step that unifies Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs. variant patterns in pulse logs and validates prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a PowerShell TIC experiment script that analyzes pulse logs, classifies content as invariant/variant, and measures prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC_RESULTS.md\",\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# Get recent pulse logs\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs for experiment\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs...\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n# Extract content patterns from each pulse\r\nfunction Extract-Patterns($content) {\r\n    $patterns = @{\r\n        Goals = @()\r\n        Actions = @()\r\n        Insights = @()\r\n        Files = @()\r\n        Metadata = @()\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goal references\r\n    if ($content -match '(Phase \\d|Goal|Active|Completed|Pending)') {\r\n        $patterns.Goals += $Matches[0]\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract file references\r\n    $fileMatches = [regex]::Matches($content, '(?:[a-zA-Z0-9_/]+\\.(?:md|ps1|txt))')\r\n    $patterns.Files = $fileMatches.Value | Select-Object -Unique\r\n    \r\n    # Extract action keywords\r\n    $actionKeywords = @('Create', 'Update', 'Implement', 'Analyze', 'Measure', 'Validate', 'Complete')\r\n    foreach ($kw in $actionKeywords) {\r\n        if ($content -match $kw) {\r\n            $patterns.Actions += $kw\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract insight markers\r\n    if ($content -match '(?:Insight|Hypothesis|Finding|Key)') {\r\n        $patterns.Insights += $Matches[0]\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $patterns\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Compare adjacent pulses for invariants\r\nfunction Find-Invariants($pulse1, $pulse2) {\r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Goals are invariant if unchanged\r\n    if ($pulse1.Patterns.Goals.Count -gt 0 -and \r\n        $pulse2.Patterns.Goals.Count -gt 0) {\r\n        $overlap = Compare-Object $pulse1.Patterns.Goals $pulse2.Patterns.Goals\r\n        if ($overlap.Count -eq 0) {\r\n            $invariants += \"Goals\"\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += \"Goals\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Files are invariant if same references\r\n    if ($pulse1.Patterns.Files.Count -gt 0 -and \r\n        $pulse2.Patterns.Files.Count -gt 0) {\r\n        $overlap = Compare-Object $pulse1.Patterns.Files $pulse2.Patterns.Files\r\n        if ($overlap.Count -eq 0) {\r\n            $invariants += \"Files\"\r\n        } else {\r\n            $variants += \"Files\"\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariants = $invariants\r\n        Variants = $variants\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Analyze all pulses\r\n$analysis = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulseFiles.Count; $i++) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulseFiles[$i].FullName -Raw\r\n    $analysis += @{\r\n        File = $pulseFiles[$i].Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Patterns = Extract-Patterns $content\r\n        Index = $i\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate invariant/variant transitions\r\n$transitions = @()\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $analysis.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $comparison = Find-Invariants $analysis[$i] $analysis[$i+1]\r\n    $transitions += @{\r\n        From = $analysis[$i].File\r\n        To = $analysis[$i+1].File\r\n        Invariants = $comparison.Invariants\r\n       \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 15:39:01\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774295522968}}
